125 12-15 - @lorettalynnmx  2005. Wish we could watch these guys race 125’s together again today!

#73 tries… and you wondered why I was so pumped! When I did this, I had no idea what I was doing or if it even had a chance at going in. I thought if the idea one night and went to Menards the next morning having no real idea what I would get, then putting something together quick and going to a friend’s house to give it a shot… literally! I ended up with a snow shovel, some metal air duct and two rolls of duct tape, then found some pvc pipe later, once I did some testing! I couldn’t believe the distance I could get out of this setup. I didn’t mean to, but I had the shovel taped where the fender actually worked as a spring; the best things usually happen by accident! I want to try a few more “different” ideas, like this, once I start riding again this summer. Any guesses on what I’m thinking?? 🤔💭

‼️MEGA CAMP COACH‼️
Nobody has more fun on a dirt bike than Oklahoma's own @bq365! There aren't many people in the world that are compared to Kevin Windham when it comes to natural talent, style and ability. Brett Cue is one of those few. Brett's love for riding dirt bikes and friendly personality has been winning over fans in recent years as his talent has been pushing him into the spotlight. From building pools in Oklahoma to racing and competing in contests with the most famous riders in the world - BQ is the poster child for having a raw passion for dirt bikes.

Brett grew up racing in a family of racers and has raced @lorettalynnmx in A, B, C, AND Vet Classes! After years of racing and competing at the highest level, Brett transitioned to freeriding and building content for social media and his sponsors.  Brett first started riding at the age of 10, and hasn't stopped since! A local racer turned pro in 2010, Brett has run the full spectrum of racing and even competed in the Best Whip competition at the 2013 Monster Energy Cup. With a history of working with great coaches; Brett has been working with young athletes since 2004. Teaching and working with them to build technique, form, and ultimately speed. 

Brett is joining the @redlineoil @mega_camp presented by @guts_racing_inc and @atindustriesinc family for the first time year and we are so excited to have him! We will miss Brad and Giulia DePrenger who were unable to make it this year due to a scheduling conflict. We know that Brett will be a great addition to the team and has a WEALTH of knowledge in the sport of motocross!

For sale - 2022 Honda CRF450. This bike is in awesome shape. I didn’t ride it as much as normal because of my knee. I got it at the beginning of last year but was on and off the bike dealing with the knee. In September, I had a surgery to get everything ready for the new ACL. I rode twice between September and when I had surgery to actually fix the ACL in December. I was off the bike until May and rode it a few times since. 

The bike has brand new wheels and tires, new chain and sprocket, new exhaust, new filter, new seat cover, (all off my 23), plastic and graphics that were ridden with once and brand new forks and shock from the 23. Aside from that, it has random parts from Works Connection, including radiator braces, as well as ODI bars and grips, Acerbis chain block and Rekluse clutch cover. I changed the clutch plates and brake pads on both ends 2-3 rides ago. Oil has been changed every 2 rides with Bel Ray. This is a well taken care of bike that will last somebody a long time. Plenty of extra stuff to include with it! Dm me if you’re interested. Serous buyers only, please!

I opened the mailbox today and had a big surprise. These photos were taken at the Gloss Mountains in Oklahoma back in 2003. This is the place I grew up riding and only place I rode from 1996 to around 2000. It was 3500 acres of awesome where my dad built two tracks and we had more natural jumps and hillclimbs than you’ll find anywhere else - you could go about as big as your imagination would let you! Travis was actually wanting to buy some of it after he went there for the first time in 1999 but was never able to. Ah, what could have been! 

Thanks to Jim Platek for these awesome photos of some times riding with my dad, Blake, Grant , Max, Dennis and some other close friends that I’ll never forget. There were a few jumps that Travis, Kenny and the whole group tried hundreds of times but never cleared. I just know these 450’s could make them… Wish I could buy some land out there and bring “the mountains” back to life!
